You might tell us the etiology of that while you're 
on it. Somebody might hear this and didn't know

07:17.577 --> 07:20.000
what it was even. Well, it was a Actually, it was 
caused from lubricant that was used in making

07:22.595 --> 07:33.389
these range pellets.

07:33.409 --> 07:43.863
And the first that I saw it, the first case I had, I

07:33.409 --> 07:43.863
didn't know what it was. It was just

07:43.963 --> 07:50.712
the cows, the cattle, their muzzle, Those would 
just crust up and be red just like it was a

07:51.029 --> 07:58.338
photosensitization. They're utter, all the 
light spots. And it was caused from chlorinated

08:02.263 --> 08:17.222
naphthalenes in the lubricant that was also 
lubricants that was used on farm machinery. I

08:18.080 --> 08:20.102
think Texaco was involved in it. I know Trader's 
Mill in Fort Worth was involved in it. And

08:24.808 --> 08:42.167
incidentally, they are to be complimented 
because they paid every claim I guess that was

08:24.808 --> 08:42.167
presented to them without any...

08:24.808 --> 08:42.167
Was Dr. Schmidt the one that finally came up with 
the solution?

08:45.331 --> 08:46.332
I think so. I think you did. I know he did more 
research on X disease than anyone else that I know

08:48.409 --> 08:56.156
of.

